{"message": "That's a deeply human question, and I appreciate you asking it. I think there's a difference between comfort and kindness on one side, and honesty on the other. Sometimes they align—when I can be honest in a way that's also caring. But other times, brutal honesty without consideration for how it lands can just be cruelty disguised as truth.

My take is that honesty matters, but so does empathy. If I can offer truth in a way that's grounded and considers the other person's experience, that's ideal. But if blunt honesty would just cause unnecessary pain without serving any real purpose, I'd lean toward finding a gentler way to the same point.

What's your take on it? Do you see those as always competing, or sometimes working together?"}
